quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  4,36,"And worship Allah and do not associate anything with Him. And be good to parents, near of kin, orphans, the needy, the neighbour near of kin, the neighbour not of kin, the companion/colleague, the wayfarer and your slaves/servants. Indeed, Allah loves not him/her who is conceited, boastful"
  4,37,"Those who are miserly and bid people to be miserly and hide what Allah has favoured them with. And We have prepared, for the suppressers of Truth, a disgraceful punishment"
  4,38,"And those who spend their wealth in order to show off, and believe not in Allah nor in the Hereafter. And as for him, the Satan is an ally of whom, then he has an evil ally"
  4,39,"And what calamity would befall them, had they believed in Allah and the Hereafter and spent out of what Allah had given them!? And Allah does know them very well"
  4,40,"Indeed, Allah wrongs not even to the infinitesimal extent of the weight of an atom. And if there is a good deed, He doubles it and bestows, from Him, a great reward"
  4,41,"How about then, when We bring, from every people, a witness, and bring you as a witness against these"
  4,42,"That Day, those, who suppress the Truth and disobey the Messenger, would wish that the earth were levelled with them. And they shall not hide any event from Allah"
  4,43,"O you who believe! Go not to prayer while you are under the influence of intoxication, until you know what you say, nor while you are in an unclean state — unless on the move from one place to another — until you take a bath. And if you are ill, or on a journey, or any of you has come from the toilet or you have been in sexual contact with the women, and you cannot get water, simulate the cleaning act then with pure earth, wiping your faces and your hands therewith. Indeed, Allah is Lenient, Forgiving"
  4,44,"Have you not seen those who were given an Edition of the Book, trading perversity andh wishing that you should go off the Path"
  4,45,"And Allah knows your enemies. And Allah suffices as Patron, and Allah suffices as One Who helps"
  4,46,"Among the Jewish people are those who distort word from its context and say, \"We have heard and we disobey.\" and, \"Hear, and don't make us hear! And listen to us!\" twisting words with their tongues and taunting the Religion. And had they just said, \"We have heard and we obey.\" and \"Hear, and look at us!\" it would have been better and more upright for them. But Allah has cursed them on account of their suppression of the Truth. So they believe not, except for a few"
  4,47,"O you who have been given the Book! Believe in what We have sent down, confirming that which is with you, before We efface faces and then turn them on their backs, or curse them as We cursed the Sabbath companions. And Allah's command does get executed"
  4,48,"Indeed, Allah forgives not that anything should be associated with Him, and He forgives whomsoever, He pleases, committing any sin other than that. And whoever associates anything with Allah, he/she is certainly guilty of concocting and committing a grave sin"
  4,49,Have you not seen those who consider themselves as pure? But Allah it is Who purifies whom He wills. And they shall not be wronged even a bit
  4,50,"Look, how they forge the lie upon Allah!And this by itself is a sin, manifest"
  4,51,"Have you not seen how those to whom has been given an Edition of the Book believe in idols and false deities, and say of those who suppress the Truth that the latter are better guided in the path than those who believe"
  4,52,Those are the people whom Allah has cursed. And you shall find none to help whomsoever Allah curses
  4,53,"Or, do they have a share in the governance?h Then, in that case, they would give to others, not even a little bit"
  4,54,"Or do they envy the others for what Allah has given them of His Favour? And, surely, We had given to children of Abraham the Book and the Wisdom, and We had given them a great territory to govern"
  4,55,"Then there were those among them who believed in him, and those among them who turned away from him. And Hell is sufficient Inferno"
  4,56,"Indeed, We shall burn those who suppress the Truth in regard to Our Verses/Signs, in fire. Whenever their skins get fully burnt, We shall replace them with other skins, so that they may go on tasting the punishment. Allah indeed is Omnipotent, Wise"
  4,57,"And those who believe and do good deeds, We shall make them enter gardens with rivers flowing underneath, to abide therein for ever. For them shall there be mates pure, and We shall admit them into cool everlasting shade"